      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CALEDONIAN RANGER (1) led and kept going to score by 2.8m at Cranbourne last start so has the gate speed to take advantage of the ace draw. He is two from two at this circuit and distance so can go right on with the job. CALYPSO MISTRESS (3) has been racing well of late. Overcame a wide barrier on the second line when winning last month at Melton and came from there again when third at her latest appearance at Ballarat. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw. Big chance. OCEAN AVENUE (5) owns a good record at this distance and could be ready to win again after placing in his last three outings. ASMILEANDAWINX (7) is good enough to measure up in this line-up if things go his way.",
